# scrollbar-width and hidden scrollbars

`scrollbar-width` is not supported in Safari, Safari on iOS, Samsung Internet, or Chrome before 121. Do not set it alone when hiding scrollbars.

Use all three layers (same pattern as `src/global-styles/1-reset.scss`):

```scss
// ❌ BAD — linter / compat warnings; no effect in Safari
.panel {
  overflow-x: auto;
  scrollbar-width: none;
}

// ✅ GOOD
.panel {
  overflow-x: auto;
  -ms-overflow-style: none; /* IE and legacy Edge */
}

.panel::-webkit-scrollbar {
  /* Chrome, Safari, Opera, Edge Chromium */
  display: none;
  width: 0;
  height: 0;
}

@supports (scrollbar-width: none) {
  .panel {
    scrollbar-width: none; /* Firefox; Chromium 121+ */
  }
}
```

- **WebKit** (`::-webkit-scrollbar`): required for Safari and most Chromium scrollbars.
- **Firefox / Chromium 121+**: gate `scrollbar-width: none` inside `@supports (scrollbar-width: none)`.
- **Legacy Edge / IE**: `-ms-overflow-style: none` when the element needs it outside the global reset.

Do not remove `::-webkit-scrollbar` rules when adding `@supports`; they cover different engines.
